Diligence Statement: In the creation of this document, we used Claude 3.5, 4, 4.1 gemeni pro, qwen, open ai chatgpt grok, and google translate to generate the document. We also used the AI-powered tool, AI Fluency Levels (AFL), to identify the levels of AI literacy in India. The AI literacy levels are categorized into four levels: AI Aware, AI User, AI Validator, and AI Orchestrator. Each level represents a different stage in the AI adoption journey, with the highest level being AI Orchestrator. The levels are designed to provide a comprehensive understanding of the current state of AI adoption in India and the potential impact of AI on society. We believe that this document will serve as a valuable resource for policymakers, educators, and other stakeholders interested in understanding the current state of AI adoption in India and the potential impact of AI on society.